  "2026-06-06T04:45:12.384Z",codex-telemetry-batch,"Kickoff: implementing pm telemetry status/flush/stats/clear command surface, MCP/contracts wiring, token-efficient output defaults, and full validation as part of one combined observability PR with pm-t4wb."
  "2026-06-06T05:04:53.481Z",codex-telemetry-batch,"Implemented pm telemetry local analytics command surface: pm telemetry status/flush/stats/clear wired in CLI registration, command help content, SDK contracts, MCP pm_run action=telemetry dispatch, and refreshed contracts snapshot. New command behavior: status reports queue depth + endpoint + last flush metadata; stats groups queued events by command with --limit; flush triggers inline queue flush and reports before/after depth; clear disables telemetry and removes runtime queue/state artifacts. Added dedicated unit coverage at tests/unit/commands/telemetry-command.spec.ts plus release-readiness + MCP contract parity tests. Manual temp-dir smoke (dist CLI) executed status/stats/flush/clear/status in a fresh PM_PATH+PM_GLOBAL_PATH sandbox and confirmed clear leaves telemetry disabled with queue_entries=0 and no runtime telemetry artifacts."
